    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "I'm thinking we can keep a stack of the other trie nodes from the leaf in memory.  Once a trie node is full or known that no other nodes will be added to it we remove it off the stack.  \r\n\r\nI'm thinking that we will need one branch/extension node per depth level, and as we need to open up a new branch/extension node at a level that does not include the next level's node then the node replaced and all nodes at deeper levels can be written to disk.  This will be _much_ easier with binary tries.",
